rComments: He is a passionate, caring man who genuinely enjoys what he is teaching. The lectures can be quite dry but are certainly doable. Exams/Assignment were fairly easy.

He has a great deal of knowledge in the area of discussion; however, he does a poor job of conveying that knowledge articulately to the class during lectures. He speaks slowly and in a monotone voice, and this makes listening attentively difficult. I would, however, recommend this course because it was relatively easy.

Great Prof. Old-school style. REALLY nice and helpful. Great anecdotal stories. I totally recommend him. Easy "A" if you take good notes in all his lectures..and readings are minimal (like, 4-5 pages per lecture).
Helpful, insightful, well organized and speaks with a pace very convenient for note-taking. Fully recommend this professor.

He is an amazing professor, i like his old school style because he spends more time teaching and less time fliping the slides. I think he was my best prof this year. He made the class enjoyable and interesting used current events..well i have not taken the final yet so i may change my mind after ...lol im joking he is a fair prof :)

great professor! lectures at a moderate pace so you are able to take good notes. tests & assignments are fair and reflect course material. overall a great learning experience taking any of his classes.
